$ SQLite function: regexp
@ regexp

Search for records with → development/regular-expressions[regular expressions].

`regexp` is not a built in function, the functionality needs to be imported. In the → development/databases/SQLite/shell[SQLite shell], with a
→ development/databases/SQLite/shell/load[`.load /usr/lib/sqlite3/pcre.so`] directive.


gh|about-sqlite|/functions/regexp.sql||


In → Linux/distributions/Ubuntu[Ubuntu], `pcro.so` might be installed with
code {
sudo apt-get install sqlite3-pcre
code }

